<title>SWITZERLAND: Ascom slips to 1996 group net loss.</title>
<headline>Ascom slips to 1996 group net loss.</headline>
<dateline>BERNE 1997-04-16</dateline>
<text>
<p>Calendar 1996</p>
<p>				    (million Sfr unless stated)</p>
<p> Group net			128 loss	  vs 25 profit</p>
<p> Dividend			 nil		 vs five percent</p>
<p>Note - Full name in Ascom Holding AG.  </p>
<p> Turnover		     2,942	     vs 2,956</p>
<p> Operating profit		94	     vs    75</p>
<p> Pre-tax			  109 loss	vs    50 profit</p>
<p> Net financial expense	 41	     vs    11</p>
<p>Other costs and income, incl  min interests		  162 loss	vs    14 loss</p>
<p> Taxes			     19	     vs    25</p>
<p> Write-offs		     180	     vs   189</p>
<p> Changes in provisions	163	     vs   (29)</p>
<p> Cash flow			215	     vs   185</p>
<p> New orders		   2,767	     vs 2,819</p>
<p> Order backlog		  914	     vs 1,054</p>
<p> Investment in plant	  130	     vs   118</p>
<p> Net debt			 470	     vs   638</p>
<p> Number of employees     11,739	     vs 12,487</p>
<p>Note - Ascom said the net loss stemmed from restructuring costs of 152 million Swiss francs taken to support its future focus on selected segments of telecommunications and service automation. In light of its on-site paging venture with Ericsson, in which it holds 70 percent, Nira company results were consolidated for the first time. Divestitures included its Rohrpost division, the Siscat plastics company and Ascom Warren, a U.S. energy systems unit.</p>
<p>-- Zurich newsroom +41 1 631 7340</p>
